comments.text: It was loud. I hated the fuck of it. I never liked these places. It made me feel like I was being watched by everyone. I felt unsafe. I felt insecure. Far away she was. Not stunning, not the most beautiful woman. Yet a silent one, a scared one. Trying not to be in a visible spot, I moved away from the big crowd. Across the room she was. Without a fuck in mind, and for some unrelated reasons we had to move closer. But as I got closer, the pain started. It was slightly tingling at first. But as we moved closer, it skyrocketed. I started approaching without anything in mind and not for her at all. But I could not stop moving toward her once I started. And here she moved towards me too. Is that real? Did she actually move toward me? I had to know. Was this even ever an option? Towards her I moved closer. But the pain, oh from the pain. I was here for a mission. I cannot get closer. I should not be seen. I am an alien here. And I liked being an alien. But now, I fucking wished to be a peer of her. I wished to be in the same species. I should not slip. I should not forget the reason I am here. But her eyes were looking at me. No fucking way they were. I have nothing to lose. I had to know. Was she looking at me? Noway, did she just approach me? It hurt badly. I never saw her kind as superiors. In fact, I despised how easy they had it. I loved where I was. I respected my road and accepted my inheritance. But closer she moved. And much closer I moved. Slowly approaching her. She smiled. And with that smile, my world collapsed. I could not tell who I was. Why am I actually here? Was happiness ever an option? This changes everything. Or does it? What about the rest of the cockroaches dying in the bit. You are here on a mission. Or are you even who you think you are. It all did not matter. I just had to see more of that smile. I had to get closer. I had to know. Closer I moved towards her. I was in the middle of the stage, around all of the couples dancing. I came face to face with her. Her smile was worth it. I looked at it for so long to collect as much happiness as I can, for I know I will never have this again. It should have never been this way, it cannot ever be this way. She knows it. I know it. But I can see that she is smiling at me. I had to know. I implied that I am up to a dance, and waited in absolute fear for her response. She knew that it cannot ever be. It is as obvious as the sun. for a hundred reasons it just cannot ever happen. Yet I did not care. And I had to know. She raised her hands towards me. Of course she would have regretted it and saw the mistake she made right after that moment. But for that moment, she did not care either. And then I knew. It was an option. In a different world I could have danced with her. I approached her hand with mine slowly. Not caring of the consequences. But just before we touch. I walked away. We could have never danced. Perhaps if we could, I would have thrown it all off the window and just danced with her, risking everything. But It was never going to happen even if we tried. I was like a hologram in her world and we could have never danced. But at least I knew. And now the pain is greater. It was much easier when I did not know. When I had no other option. But now I know that it is possible to be happy. And it aches. And who knows, this for certain is better. Maybe if we had touched, I would have scratched her soft skin with my muddy-working hands. Maybe if we started dancing she would have seen how awful I was in it. Maybe if she got close she would have seen how ugly I am and How stinky my smell is. It for sure is better to leave it with just knowing that maybe there might have been a chance for me in a different world.

comments.text:
To everyone who's studying with this music:

Checklist: 

• A bottle of water, at least 1 liter. Your brain works better if it has enough water and drinking helps you to concentrate💧



• Your charger. You sometimes don't even notice that your device's battery is going down, so better have it plugged in all the time🔋



• Your headphones. You will be able to focus more with headphones, because it blocks background noises. Also, if it's a late night study session, you won't wake up anyone🎧



• a tea or coffee. Coffee keeps you awake, green or black tea can make you feel more awake as well.☕



• Your study/work stuff:  your laptop/tablet/phone , a few pens, paper or whatever you need.⌨



•Anything else you could need, what about a heat pad, a blanket, a good lamp, your pet so you have a study buddy 🐈





Reminder : After an hour, you should stand up and walk a bit around. Better stop the music or put on different music for the break. Open your window, even if it's cold outside. Fresh air will make it better, trust me. 

You could also lay your head down on your desk for ten minutes and listen to a podcast. Or, if you have to read a book, listen to the audiobook of it. You can also listen to the audiobook while doing another thing, that's even better than listening to music while reading the book.



I hope y'all had a good day, if not, that's okay too. Remember to take care of yourself and try to get some sleep tonight 😴🧸stayhomeplanet-orange-purple-ring
(please repost this on any other video you listen to while studying and spread the love♥)
